Representatives of Chinese Business Chamber of Tanzania have paid a courtesy call on Her Excellency President Samia Suluhu at the State House  in Chamwino, Dodoma, Wednesday and discussed various issues pertaining to investments. According to a State House statement issued today, the business community assured the Head of State that it will cooperate with the sixth phase government  in the areas of investment and people's welfare. They have assured that over 800 Chinese companies  are ready to invest in Tanzania. The targeted areas, according to the statement, are mobile phone industry, human medicine, cars and industrial parks. Another area they are ready to invest is education sector as they plan  to establish  a programme which will enable Tanzanians to study at various  to varsities and colleges in China.